T1  - Earnings information conveyed by dividend initiations and omissions
AU  - Healy, Paul M.
AU  - Palepu, Krishna G.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
SP  - 149
EP  - 175
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/09/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(88)90059-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X88900591
AB  - Firms that initiate dividend payments have positive earnings changes both before and after the dividend policy change, while those omitting dividend payments have negative earnings changes. Subsequent earnings changes are positively related to the dividend announcement return, and stock price reactions at subsequent earnings announcements are smaller than usual, suggesting that these earnings changes are partially anticipated at the dividend announcement. The results indicate that investors interpret announcements of dividend initiations and omissions as managers' forecasts of future earnings changes.
ER  - 

